Ogbonnaya Ikokwu, Umuahia Governor Okezie Ikpeazu of Abia State has sacked the Commissioner for Transport, Mr Ekele Nwaohanmuo. He also sacked the transition committee chairman of the  Umenneochi Local Goverment Area, Mr Mathew Ibe,  his counterparts in Aba South, Cherechi Nwogu; and Aba North, Victor Ubani. Ikpeazu announced their sacking on Sunday in a statement by his Chief of Staff, Anthony Agbazuere. The statement added that the General Manager of the Traffic and Indiscipline Management Agency of Abia State, Mr Bright Ikokwu, was also suspended. No reason was given for the sacking and suspension of the government appointees. Agbazuere stated that the governor had approved the appointment of Mr Tony Nwanmuo and Godswill Nwonoruo as commissioner-nominees. The statement read in part, “The deputy chairmen of the affected council areas are to take over the administration of the councils. “The deputy chairpersons are to liaise with the Head of Service to set up task force teams to check environmental indiscipline and other vices in their areas.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 